The paper deals with algorithms for analyzing patterns in data streams, which is a topic that falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The problem of identifying a longest substring of two data streams that forms a near-alignment under the edit distance involves information theory (cs.IT) and combinatorics (cs.DM). The simultaneous streaming model used in the paper is a computational complexity concept (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the design of data stream algorithms, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
